@NODE main  "GTBTranslatorPPC© 2003 User Manual:"
@TOC "Contents"
  This manual is intended as an aid in using the @{B}GTBTranslatorPPC ©@{UB}
  system.  It is not intended to be used as a primer on the SmallTalk language
  or C or @{" GadToolsBox " LINK "gadtoolsbox"}.  @{B}GTBTranslatorPPC ©@{UB} is a program that takes the
  output files of @{" GadToolsBox " LINK "gadtoolsbox"} V2.0b & translates their contents into either
  a C source file or an AmigaTalk source file.

  The main reason I wrote these program(s) is because I got tired of
  editing the generated C source files from @{" GadToolsBox " LINK "gadtoolsbox"}.  It takes at least
  two hours per project simply to make the output from @{" GadToolsBox " LINK "gadtoolsbox"} readable
  & compilable.  There are also several problems that have to be corrected
  in order for the generated source to run correctly as well.  @{B}GTBTranslatorPPC@{UB}
  will also generate a MakeFile & the Locale header file associated with
  your C-source code.  The generated makefile has to be renamed by you because
  your source directory might already have one present, so GTBTranslatorPPC will
  generate the makefile as @{FG SHINE}ProjectName.make@{FG TEXT}.
  
  Currently, GTBTranslatorPPC is intended to generate simple, one-window
  GUIs.
  
  In order to use GTBTranslatorPPC, you have to have the @{" Requirements " LINK "requirement"}.
      
