@NODE startup "Running the system:"
@PREV main

  The GTBTranslatorPPC system is invoked by typing the command @{FG SHINE}GTBTranslatorPPC@{FG TEXT}
  or by clicking on the GTBTranslatorPPC icon.  The main GUI should be self-
  explanatory -- simply enter the two required file names & click on the 
  task button that you wish to have the program perform.

  After you enter your *.gui source filename & your *.ini destination filename,
  clicking on the @{B}Make @{U}P@{UU}roject@{UB} button will:

     1. GTBScannerPPC will read & parse the *.gui file & produce the *.ini file,
        after you have supplied any additional information you require into
        the second GUI Requester for Project Information.
     
  Next, you can edit the *.ini file (if necessary).  Finally, you can
  check the @{B}Generate @{U}S@{UU}MakeFile@{UB} or @{B}Generate @{U}L@{UU}ocale@{UB} 
  Check Gadgets & click on the @{B}Output @{U}C@{UU} Source@{UB} button.
      
     2. @{B}GTBTranslatorPPC@{UB} will read the *.ini file & the GenC.template file & generate
        the final C-source file, as well as a MakeFile & LocaleFile (if
        you checked them in the GUI).
 
  Now you can edit the MakeFile or Locale *.cd file by pressing:
     @{B}Edit @{U}M@{UU}akeFile@{UB} or
     @{B}Edit L@{U}o@{UU}cale@{UB} button Gadgets.
	
  The @{B}Output @{U}A@{UU}migaTalk Source@{UB} button will generate Smalltalk code for the
  AmigaTalk programming system (when it's ready).

  NOTE:  The ToolTypes ListView Gadget is read-only.
       
@ENDNODE

